<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Envoy Arriving in India For Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lakshman Jayakodi, Sri Lankan Minister for Buddhist Sasana,
Culture and Religion Affairs, is arriving here Tuesday on a three-
day visit, the PTI said.
</P>
<P>
Jayakodi is scheduled to call on Indian Prime Minister Atal
Bihari Vajpayee and is also likely to meet Indian External Affairs
Minister Jaswant Singh during his stay, an Indian foreign office
spokesperson was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Jayakodi will be accompanied by K Balapatabendi, secretary to
the Sri Lankan President and S. Bandaranaike, Sri Lanka's
ambassador to France, the PTI added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
