the Israeli regime responsible for the life of the Iranians, who
are said to be still alive in Israeli prisons.
</P>
<P>
Kharrazi said Israel has not denied the abduction of the four
Iranian nationals but has since maintained total silence and
imposed news blackout on the topic and consistently ignored
official pleas by Iran for their freedom.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, Iranian Foreign Ministry spokesman Hamid Reza Asefi
also condemned Israel for the abduction and called on international
organizations to help secure the release of the Iranians.
</P>
<P>
Iran has refused to recognize the legitimacy of the Israeli
regime since the 1979 Islamic revolution. It also calls for armed
struggle against Israeli occupation of Arab and Islamic lands.
