<HEADLINE> Uruguay's Meat Exports Go Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, July 4 (Xinhua)-- Uruguay's meat exports reached
250 million U.S. dollars in year 2000's first six-month period,
increasing by 26 percent with regard to 1999's same period, the
National Institute of Meats (INAC) reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In the indicated period, volumes of bovine meat placement came
to 146,894 tons, a 34 percent growth relative to 1999's same lapse.
Main purchasers were countries of the North American Free Trade
Agreement (NAFTA), the Common Southern Market (Mercosur) and the
European Union.
</P>
<P>
Exports of ovine meat were of 9,309 tons, whose main
destinations are the European Union and Mercosur.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Uruguay exported a total of 270,000 tons of meat,
with an income of 434 million dollars. 
