<HEADLINE> Time Not Ripe for African Parliament: S. African FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 4 (Xinhua) -- South Africa supported the
establishment of an African parliament which was possible, but the
continent was not yet ready for it, Foreign Affairs Minister
Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"We must take steps to get there, but we are not yet ready to
go into the United States of Africa... we think it is possible,"
