Dlamini-Zuma said the continent still needed to look at
consultative forums to discuss issues of common interest,
including an African court and central bank.
</P>
<P>
She said the forthcoming Organizations of African Unity summit,
due to be held in Togo on July 10-12, would further look at how
the continent could consolidate its unity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
