<HEADLINE> UAE One of Top Waste Producers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The United Arab Emirates (UAE)is
among one of the world's top domestic waste producers, with the per
household waste reaching annually 730 kilograms in Abu Dhabi and
725 kilograms in Dubai.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the domestic waste, additional waste comes from the
roads and street littering, gardens and trash dumped in the sea and
on beaches, according to a report by the official WAM news agency.
</P>
<P>
The report said the increasing amount of domestic waste has
imposed strains on the municipalities and the problem is just
partly solved by converting organic wastes into fertilizers, while
wastes like cans, paper and glass are recycled.
</P>
<P>
The average domestic waste per family in the U.S., according to
the report, is 710 kilograms, Australia an average of 690 kilograms
and Britain about 300 kilograms. 
</P>
