is ready to produce any additional quantities of oil to be agreed
upon by OPEC oil ministers," he added.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia called on Monday to raise oil output by 500,000
barrels per day in the next few weeks to bring down prices now
standing at about 30 U.S. dollars per barrel.
</P>
<P>
As of July, according to statistics, the quota of Saudi Arabia,
the world's top oil producer, is 8.25 million barrels per day,
while the quota of Iran, OPEC's second largest producer, has also
increased by 104,000 barrels, reaching 3.727 million barrels per
day.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting in Vienna last month, the OPEC agreed to increase
output by 708,000 barrels per day starting last Saturday. But since
the announcement, oil prices have gone up. 
</P>
