<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Starts to Distribute 10,000 Tons of Relief Food </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian government and
non- governmental organizations (NGOs) are moving about 10,200
tons of grain for distribution in drought-affected areas in the
country.
</P>
<P>
The Federal Disaster Prevention and Preparedness Commission
(DPPC) with the Ministry of Agriculture Tuesday said that of the
total food aid under delivery, DPPC's share amounted to 5,848
tons, while the remaining 4,335 tons were contributed by NGOs.
</P>
<P>
The largest chunk, about 3,130 tons, is destined for the needy
in the central Amhara State, while the states of Somali and
Oromia will each get more than 1,900 tons, DPPC said.
</P>
<P>
It said that transportation and distribution activities are
being carried out in a coordinated manner in the areas.
</P>
<P>
Latest survey shows that Ethiopia, hit by drought in the last
three years, has some 10 million people facing starvation.
</P>
