<HEADLINE> Tourist Arrival in Cyprus Up in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The number of travellers who visited
Cyprus in May this year increased by 16.4 percent to 372,087,
compared to the same month last year, the Cyprus News Agency
reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The number of tourists increased from about 273,000 to nearly
300,000. Over half of them came from Britain.
</P>
<P>
Other tourists are mainly from Germany, Sweden, Russia, Norway,
Greece and Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
The overwhelming majority of tourists, 81.8 percent, came from
European Union countries.
</P>
<P>
Between January and May, over 800,000 tourists came to Cyprus
compared to 711,670 in the same period in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 50,000 Cypriots returned home from trips abroad in May,
compared to just over 35,000 in May the year before.
</P>
<P>
The tourist industry plays a key role in the economy of the
east Mediterranean country, accounting for more than 20 percent of
the
country's gross domestic product (GDP).  
</P>
</TEXT>
