<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Troops Kill 23 Rebels in New Offensive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan troops on Tuesday
launched a new offensive and killed at least 23 Tamil Tiger rebels
in the northern Jaffna peninsula, a government statement said.
</P>
<P>
Troops launched the offensive early on Tuesday to destroy a
rebel bunker line south of Nagarkovil, said the statement, adding
that troops ambushed rebel reinforcements killing a large number
of rebels of Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE).
</P>
<P>
"Twenty three terrorist dead bodies have been recovered so far
together with 17 T56 assault rifles, two light machine guns and
miscellaneous military equipment," said the statement.
</P>
<P>
It said one officer and one soldier died in action while three
officers and 34 soldiers were wounded.
</P>
<P>
The casualties on both sides are expected to be higher as the
operation is in progress.
</P>
<P>
Jaffna was the scene of fierce fighting until the end of May
when the military deployed new weapons and more troops and stalled
a "rolling offensive" by the LTTE to recapture their former
stronghold of Jaffna peninsula.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels have been fighting for a separate homeland
called Eelam for minority Tamils in Sri Lanka's north and east
since 1983. More than 60,000 people have been killed in the
conflict. 
</P>
</TEXT>
