<HEADLINE> Vietnamese Communist Party Concludes Plenary Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The Tenth Plenary Session of the
Eighth Central Committee of the Communist Party of Vietnam (CPV)
concluded here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The CPV's plenary session discussed and approved the drafts of
the political report and other documents to be presented at the
Ninth National Congress of the CPV.
</P>
<P>
According to a communique of the Plenum, the members of CPV
Central Committee focused on discussing the following four major
issues:
</P>
<P>
-- Evaluation of domestic and international situation, and then
defining the opportunities, challenges and threats Vietnam will be
faced with in 21st century;
</P>
<P>
-- Ownership issues covering different economic sectors;
</P>
<P>
-- An independent and self-reliant economy and international
integration, and
</P>
<P>
-- The Party's building plan, tasks and solutions in the new
situation.
</P>
<P>
The plenary session, which opened on June 26, 2000, has also
completed the drafts of two major documents to be presented the
Ninth National Party Congress: the report on the strategy of the
ten-year socio-economic development (2001-2010) and the plan of
the five-year socio-economic development (2001-2005); and the
report on amendments to the Party Constitution.
</P>
<P>
The plenum holds that the Ninth National Congress of the CPV to
be convened at the beginning of the 21st century will be an event
of great political and historical significance, the communique
said.
</P>
<P>
The plenary session calls on the whole party to seize the
opportunities, take up the challenges, bring the strength of the
whole people in the country into full play, go on the course of
Doi Moi (renovation promote the cause of industrialization and
modernization of the country.
</P>
<P>
The Ninth National Congress of CPV will be convened at the end
of March, 2001, Dao Duy Quat, Vice Chairman of the Ideological
Cultural Department of CPV Central Committee, said at a press
conference here on Tuesday. 
</P>
