<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Approves Over 100 Investment Projects in Five Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The Export Processing Zones
Authority of Zimbabwe has approved 113 investment projects in the
past five years.
</P>
<P>
Sixty-two of the projects are already exporting their products
while 51 of them are in various stages of implementation, said a
spokesman for the authority on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"In terms of exports, the companies which are operating have
attracted 160 million U.S. dollars," he said.
</P>
<P>
According to the spokesman, the exports are predominantly to
Europe, the United States, the Far East and the region of the
Southern African Development Community (SADC).
</P>
<P>
"The SADC component is about 11 percent of total exports," he
said.
</P>
<P>
A total of 13,780 jobs were created during the period under
review, the spokesman said, noting that due to seasonal
fluctuations, the number could rise to between 15,000 and 17,000
at the end of this month.
</P>
<P>
The biggest investment was in the agricultural and food
processing sector, which had the highest employment and export
figures, he said.
</P>
<P>
The sector boasts of 25 companies which are generating 66.3
million dollars in exports, he said, adding that the textiles and
clothing sector comes second with exports worth 43.8 million
dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
