<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> International City Conference Opens in Berlin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Over 2000 mayors and delegates
representing most of the world's largest cities attended The
International City Construction Conference Tuesday in Berlin.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony, German Chancellor Gerhard
Schroeder said that the rapid growth of cities was the most urgent
problem facing mankind in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations Secretary General Kofi Annan, who is
visiting the country and attending the conference, said that there
would have to be a radical change for big city citizens to live
and relate to each other.
</P>
<P>
"We have entered the city millennium," said Annan.
</P>
<P>
The main goal of the three-day conference is to find ways to
deal with problems with cities in the developing countries
including housing, water supply, education, health-care services
and environment protection, organizers said.
</P>
<P>
Statistics released by the conference shows that half of the
world's population are living in urban areas. By 2025, some two-
thirds of all people would be living in cities, and there will be
over 100 cities with over five million population on the world.
</P>
</TEXT>
