<HEADLINE> High Class Entry for Europe's Richest 5 furlong Handicap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The inaugural running of the 80,000
pounds Hong Kong Jockey Club Sprint, the most valuable five
furlong handicap in Europe and the centerpiece of Ascot's first
ever "Hong Kong Day" on Sunday July 30, has attracted a very high
class entry of 49 horses.
</P>
<P>
Eastern Purple, who ran a cracking race to finish a close fifth
in the King's Stand Stakes over course and distance last time, and
Tedburrow, Who came back to form with an impressive victory in the
John Smith's Extra Smooth Chipchase Stakes at Newcastle last
Saturday, are likely to head the weights for what is guaranteed to
be an ultra-competitive contest.
</P>
<P>
Other older sprinters certain to figure prominently in the
weights inlcude Halmahera, To the Roof and Dashing Blue, while
some very useful three-year-olds have also been entered, most
notably San Salvador, winner of his last three races for trainer
Jeremy Noseda.
</P>
<P>
The most appropriate winner, however, would surely be Shatin
Venture, owned by a group of Chinese restaurateurs in Glasgow.
They are hugely enthusiastic about sending their improving three-
year-old, name after Sha Tin racecourse in Hong Kong, for the big
Ascot feature.
</P>
<P>
Both Ascot Racecourse and the Hong Kong Jockey Club are
actively promoting and marketing Hong Kong Day. Douglas Erskine-
Crum, Chief Executive at Ascot, said:"We are delighted to welcome
Hong Kong Day to Ascot for the first time, giving everyone the
chance to celebrate the Year of Dragon in style."
</P>
<P>
Simon Cooper of the Hong Kong Jockey Club said:"Ascot have been
very active in ensuring that this will be a colourful and exciting
day's racing." 
</P>
