<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Roundup: Vietnam's Economic Situation Takes Favorable Turn </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's economic situation took a
favorable turn in the first half of this year with remarkable
achievements recorded in its main economic sectors.
</P>
<P>
According to the General Office of Statistics, the country's
gross domestic product (GDP) growth rate in the first half of 2000
was 6.2 percent against 4.3 percent and 6.16 percent in the
corresponding periods of 1999 and 1998, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam overcame the slow growth in the industrial production
in the 1997-1999 period. Its industrial production in the past six
months was up by 14.5 percent over the same period last year, the
highest growth rate since 1996.
</P>
<P>
Industrial production thrived not only in the state-run sector
but also in the non-state sector in the reviewed period.
</P>
<P>
The state-run sector saw a year-on-year increase of 12 percent
with Ho Chi Minh City and Da Nang City, Ha Tay, Phu Tho, Dong Nai,
Quang Ninh and Can Tho provinces registering high growth rates,
ranging from 14 percent to 30.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the foreign-invested sector posted a six-month
industrial production value of 30,576 billion Vietnamese dong (2.2
billion U.S. dollars), making up 36.9 percent of the country's
total industrial production value or a year-on-year increase of 15.
7 percent.
</P>
<P>
Outstanding achievements were also registered in the
agricultural sector. The country harvested a bumper winter-spring
rice crop with an output of more than 15.2 million tons, an
increase of more than 1.1 million tons over the same crop last
year.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam obtained an agricultural production value increase of 5.
36 percent and a forestry production value rise of 4.5 percent in
the first six months of this year.
</P>
<P>
In fisheries, aquatic produce value grew 4 percent over the
past six months with the sector's output reaching 779,000 tons, a
year-on-year increase of 6.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
Positive signs were also seen in foreign trade, which in the
past six months registered an export value of almost 6.427 billion
dollars, up by 26 percent compared to the same period last year,
and an import value of over 7.104 billion dollars or a 32.9
percent year-on-year increase. Surplus import value was about 677
million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The tourism of the country registered a sharp rise, providing
services to 1.06 million foreign tourists, an 18.17 percent
increase over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
However, there are still some unfavorable factors in Vietnam's
economy. Among other problems, a great amount of commodities,
including cement, steel, sugar, motorbikes, textile and garments,
food and foodstuffs, are unsaleable.
</P>
<P>
the low competitiveness of local products and services in terms
of quality and price, and poor economic management were the main
reasons for sluggishness in the economy.
</P>
<P>
The low purchasing power of the population is also an unstable
factor for the growth of the economy. The food and foodstuff price
drops adversely affected the purchasing power of farmers who
account for 80 percent of the country's more than 76 million
population. 
</P>
</TEXT>
