<HEADLINE> Wheat Procurement in Pakistan's Punjab Province Doubles Target </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's largest province
Punjab has procured 6.065 million tons of wheat from growers this
season, which is more than double the original purchase target.
</P>
<P>
According to the Associated Press of Pakistan, the original
target was three million tons, but due to a bumper crop the
growers offered more and more wheat for sale. Even now purchase of
the grain is continuing at the support price of 300 rupees (5.7 U.
S. dollars) per 40 kg.
</P>
<P>
As the biggest agricultural producer, Punjab will provide about
2.5 million tons of wheat to other provinces this year to meet
their requirements.
</P>
<P>
An official of Ministry of Food and Agriculture said Tuesday
that Sindh and North West Frontier Province (NWFP) will get one
million tons each, and Balochistan 500,000 tons of wheat.
</P>
<P>
The NWFP has started lifting wheat from Punjab and almost
completed its allocation while Sindh and Balochistan will start
lifting soon, he added. 
</P>
