<HEADLINE> Ugandan Ruling Movement Not to Become Political Party: President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni
Tuesday assured that the ruling National Resistance Movement can
not become a political party in the future because the Movement
contains multi- ideologies.
</P>
<P>
One party is dominated by one ideology, but the Movement is
not, he said at a press conference at the State House in the
capital Kampala, stressing that feudalists, socialists,
capitalists and others are contained in the Movement and no one
can be expelled from the system.
</P>
<P>
According to the president, heads of local administration at
various levels under the Movement government are elected through
universal suffrage in accordance with their individual merits
although they are of different ideologies.
</P>
<P>
The Ugandan Constitution defines the Movement Political System
as broad- based, inclusive and non-partisan, which features the
participatory democracy, transparency, accessibility to all
positions of leadership by all citizens. 
</P>
