<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia needs another 100,000
tons of emergency food to help relieve 10 million people hit by
drought in the country, a U.S. official has said.
</P>
<P>
Leonard Rogers, an official with the United States Agency of
International Development, said here on Monday that of an
estimated 837,000 tons of food by the World Food Program for the
year 2000, 730,000 tons have been firmly committed by donors,
"leaving over 100,000 tons in additional food requirements still
to come".
</P>
<P>
