<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Gunship Corps: Powerful Wing of China's Land Army </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 4 (Xinhua) -- After a dozen years of strenuous
training, the Land Army of the Chinese People's Liberation Army (
PLA) has developed its Gunship Corps into a powerful rapid
response force.
</P>
<P>
Over the past few years, officers and men of the Gunship Corps
have focused their training on hedgehopping, which is of great
importance for increasing the rapid response and aerial combat
capabilities of the PLA Land Army, according to army sources.
</P>
<P>
In hundreds of war games, the well-trained gunship squads have
played a unique role in promoting the integration of land and
aerial troops in modern warfare.
</P>
<P>
Nowadays, the maneuverable, all-weather gunships have become a
major means of transport for soldiers patrolling the land border,
replacing horses and sleighs.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Gunship Corps is widely used for civil and
relief missions. To date, The gunship troops have manned over 490
flights for combating forest fires and floods and recovery of
satellites, over 30,000 flights for transporting over 80,000
passengers, 941 patients and wounded people, and 8,063 tons of
goods. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
