<HEADLINE> Over 10 Super Bookstores Set Up in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 4 (Xinhua) -- More than 10 super bookstores have
come into shape in the increasingly competitive book markets of
China, according to a publishing forum held here today.
</P>
<P>
The super bookstores all boast over 10,000 varieties of books,
over 5,000 square meters of business space, and good facilities
and services.
</P>
<P>
Official figures show that Book City in Shanghai, which opened
in December 1998, was visited last year by more than 2.4 million
customers, who bought over 115 million yuan-worth of books.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Book Center in downtown Beijing sold over 140
million yuan-worth of books last year. Its sales for the first
half of this year went up 50 percent to 98 million yuan-worth.
</P>
<P>
For the better use of resources and to reduce business risks,
the super bookstores negotiated and formed an alliance at the end
of last year.
</P>
<P>
Under the terms of the alliance, the bookstores will unify book
classifications and data banks, and collectively purchase business
facilities. 
</P>
