<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S'pore Firm to Develop New Resort Home in China's Yunnan Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The project, the third resort home development project of the
Spring City Golf and Lake Resort (Spring City) in the county, will
comprise over 800 homes with a self-contained town center
featuring amenities and facilities such as swimming pool,
restaurants, community center, sports clubs and shops when fully
completed as part of the Spring City.
</P>
<P>
The Spring City comprises two 18-hole championship golf courses,
a clubhouse with lodges, resort homes, business and conference
facilities and other recreational facilities, including a newly
opened watersports center.
</P>
<P>
Keppel Land holds 40 percent stake of the Spring City while the
other shareholders include the Yunnan Provincial &AMP; Yi Liang County
Government, KMP Investments Pte Ltd, Temasek Holdings of Singapore,
Worldwide Shipping of Hong Kong and a group of Thai investors.
</P>
<P>
"We are very pleased that the golfing community in Asia have
embraced Spring City as a 'must-play' golfing destination and have
hailed its golf courses as being among the top golf courses in
this part of the world," Keppel Land said.  
</P>
