<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Launches Education Programs for Women, Children </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladeshi government has
decided to undertake quite a few programs to help the repressed
women and children, Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina told the members
of parliament Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The total government allocation for the programs is 280 million
taka (5.4 million dollars). About 8.3 million students would
benefit from the new program, said the president.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, about 2.3 million students of 17,403 schools would be
benefiting from the Food for Education program, for which the
government has allocated 3.7 billion taka (71 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
At the secondary level, under the female students' stipend
program and the Female Secondary School Assistance Project, the
government has spent 2.596 billion taka (50 million dollars) to
facilitate girls' education. In the current fiscal year, the
government has allocated 2.71 billion taka (52 million dollars)
for these projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
