<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Calls for Speeding up Border Talks With Tajikistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DUSHANBE, Tajikistan, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President
Jiang Zemin said here Tuesday that China and Tajikistan should
speed up their border talks so as to thoroughly resolve the border
issue with a solution acceptable to both sides.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the call during his formal talks with Tajik
President Emomali Rakhmonov this morning at the presidential
residence, sources with the Chinese Foreign Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
Discussing the border issue with Rakhmonov, Jiang spoke highly
of the border treaty signed by the two countries during
Rakhmonov's China trip, and described the document as "a major
step forward" in the Sino-Tajik border talks, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
"It indicated that as long as our two parties have a long-term
vision, sincerity and confidence, all the problems can be resolved
through consultation," he told Rakhmonov.
</P>
<P>
China has resolved its border problems with Khazakstan and
Kyrgrzstan, respectively, and the most part of Sino-Russian border
lines has been determined, Jiang noted.
</P>
<P>
Under such circumstances, Jiang expressed his belief that the
border issue between China and Tajikistan "can also be properly
resolved."
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that in speeding up the border negotiation process,
the two parties concerned must adopt a flexible stance in line
with the principle of equality, consultation, mutual understanding
and mutual concession in a bid to find a solution to the problem
at an earliest possible date.
</P>
<P>
Rakhmonov said that the border issue between the two countries
can be resolved "within the agreed timetable" and be properly
handled in the light of the principles as Jiang put forward.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
