<HEADLINE> Edwards to Miss European Cup Athletics Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Britain's triple jump world record
holder Jonathan Edwards Tuesday said he was pulling out of this
month's European Cup athletics meet in Gateshead to concentrate on
the Sydney Olympic Games following poor early-season form.
</P>
<P>
Edwards came in fourth palce in last Friday's Rome Golden
League meeting with a leap of 16.81 meters, well short of his
world record of 18.29 meters set at the world championships in
Gothenburg in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Edwards said: "My initial competitive performances in Bergen
and Rome have not done justice to my winter's preparation, and
this is a situation that I need to address with the utmost urgency.
</P>
<P>
