<HEADLINE> Senior Chinese, Oman Military Leaders Hold Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Fu Quanyou, chief of the general
staff of the Chinese People's Liberation Army, held talks with
Khamis Al-Kalbani, chief of staff of the Oman armed forces, here
today.
</P>
<P>
Fu, also a member of the Central Military Commission, said that
the friendly cooperation between the two countries has been
furthered since the establishment of diplomatic ties 20 years ago.
</P>
<P>
He thanked Oman for its support for China on the Taiwan issue.
</P>
<P>
Fu said that China is willing to build long-term, stable,
sincere, friendly, mutually beneficial and all-round cooperative
relations with Oman in various fields.
</P>
<P>
Fu said that he hoped that Kalbani's current visit to China
will further the friendly cooperation between the two countries
and their armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Kalbani said that the two countries share a stand on many
international issues and have maintained very good relations for a
long time.
</P>
<P>
He said that he hopes the armed forces of the two countries
will keep their high-level contacts and further the friendly
cooperation between them.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the talks, Fu held a welcoming ceremony for Kalbani.
