<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Product Quality Law to Apply to Construction Quality: Legislators </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Some top Chinese lawmakers proposed
here Tuesday that ensuring the quality of construction projects be
an integral part of the Product Quality Law.
</P>
<P>
In a panel deliberating the draft amendment to the law, Mao
Zhaoxi, a member of the Standing Committee of the National People'
s Congress (NPC), said that in recent years the poor quality of
some buildings and construction projects has caused great losses
to the State and the general public.
</P>
<P>
Mao took the quality of apartment buildings as the example. "
The price of apartments is very high, and in most cases, the
departments involved use every excuse to shake off their legal
liabilities when quality problems emerge," he said. "To protect
the legitimate rights of the general public, the Product Law
should cover quality problems of construction projects."
</P>
<P>
Li Yining and Yin Kesheng, members of the NPC Standing
Committee, voiced the same opinion when examining the draft.
</P>
<P>
Some other NPC Standing Committee members held that the Law
should stipulate that the practice of promoting products through
administrative means should be forbidden, punishments for illegal
activities should be made more severe, and the legitimate rights
of the producers of products should not be neglected.
</P>
<P>
NPC Standing Committee Member Zhang Haoruo said that though the
draft specifies that the quality supervision authorities are not
allowed to participate in the making or selling of any kind of
product, some other government departments are still involved in
such activities. Therefore, "the draft should stipulate that
government departments are not allowed to promote any product to
the general public," he suggested.
</P>
<P>
The participants in the deliberation panel agreed that the
draft not only lays down strict measures against the malpractice
of the producers of products and the quality supervision
authorities, but also protects the legitimate rights of the
customers and the producers.
</P>
<P>
The lawmakers proposed that the ongoing session of the NPC
Standing Committee pass the draft amendment to the Product Quality
Law after some minor revisions are made.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
