<HEADLINE> Healthy Development of Small Townships Urged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 4 (Xinhua) -- China's central authorities have
called for speeding up the healthy development of small townships
in the country's rural areas.
</P>
<P>
The Central Committee of the Chinese Communist Party and the
State Council have jointly issued a document entitled "Suggestions
on Promoting the Healthy Development of Small Townships,"
outlining the principles for this purpose.
</P>
<P>
The document noted that now is the time to speed up the
urbanization process, and the development of small townships
constitutes a major task for the present and future reforms and
development in the rural areas.
</P>
<P>
The development of small townships in rural areas will help
solve the deep-rooted problems in the countryside, optimize the
rural economy and expand domestic demand. It is also the way to
realize agricultural modernization.
</P>
<P>
The document stressed that the development of small townships
should proceed smoothly, and that they be planned and built in a
scientific and co-ordinated way.
</P>
<P>
In developing small townships, efforts should be made to
cultivate the economic base of the townships, the market mechanism
should be employed, and more emphasis be given to the efficient
use and protection of land, the document said. 
</P>
