<HEADLINE> Asia's UMS Provider Raises 110 Million HK Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 4 (Xinhua) -- 2bSURE.com, Asia's first provider
of unified messaging service (UMS), has received 110 million HK
dollars (14.1 million U.S. dollars) investment from four
international venture capital firms despite the difficulty in fund
raising by dotcom companies.
</P>
<P>
"This major investment will allow us to achieve our mission --
to bring the ultimate in communication power and convenience to
all of Asia," said Jerry Wu, CEO of 2bSURE.com at a press briefing
here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Based in Singapore, 2bSURE.com provides UMS that enables
subscribers to get free voice mail, fax mail and e-mail in a
single and easy-to-use inbox. Subscribers are able to retrieve and
send messages any time from any location worldwide, either through
the 2bSURE.com website or by calling a toll-free or local number.
</P>
<P>
The company has signed up more than 500,000 customers in 36
countries since it was launched last September. It has now seven
offices in Singapore, Hong Kong, Taiwan, Shanghai, Seoul, San
Francisco and other cities.
</P>
<P>
"Our goal is to stay at the forefront of the market and offer
the best unified messaging products and services to simplify the
life of users across Asia," said Wu. "We will use over 70 percent
of the new funds to accelerate capital investment and
technological development."
</P>
<P>
Wu expects 2bSURE.com to generate 3.5 million U.S. dollars in
revenue by the end of this year and become profitable in 15 months.
</P>
</TEXT>
