<HEADLINE> French Reinsurer SCOR Opens Beijing Office </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 4 (Xinhua) -- SCOR, France's largest and the
world's seventh largest reinsurer, formally opened its Beijing
office today, setting yet another milestone for its existing
business relations in China and its continued commitment to the
Asian region.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening ceremony, SCOR Chairman and Chief
Executive Officer Jacques Blondeau said that he and his colleagues
have witnessed the impressive reform and development of the China
insurance market in recent years. The opening of the market prior
to the WTO entry of China will very soon position China as a key
economic zone in the global market.
</P>
<P>
"This will bring enormous opportunities to all business sectors
including the insurance industry, and in turn will result in great
demand of services from the international reinsurance market," he
continued.
</P>
<P>
Blondeau noted that SCOR has been an active reinsurer in China
for almost 30 years and has both the commitment and the know-how
to cope with the huge potential in China.
</P>
<P>
With the opening of the Beijing office, and reinforced
resources, SCOR will be better placed to meet the challenges in
China, offering clients a broad range of products and services
including both traditional reinsurance and non-traditional
financial solutions, he said.
</P>
<P>
SCOR sees power plants such as the Three Gorges project;
petrochemical plants; infrastructure projects for railways,
underground and port development, as well as growth of the high-
tech industry as major potential areas in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
