<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Rise 0.69 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks closed up 0.69
percent, or 110.79 points, at 16,235.76 on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the market was led by telecom heavyweights, but
most investors were sidelined due to the U.S. July 4 holiday on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Of the four sub-indices of the benchmark Hang Seng Index (HSI),
only Utilities dropped 0.25 percent while Finance, Properties and
Industry &AMP; Commerce rose by 0.69 percent, 0.25 percent and 1.21
percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
The turnover on Tuesday was 8.75 billion HK dollars (1.122
billion U.S. dollars), 0.72 percent up from the volume on Monday.
</P>
<P>
China-related stocks ended higher with the Hang Seng China
Enterprises Index up 2 percent and the Hang Seng China-Affiliated
Corp Index up 1.07 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng IT Index gained slightly by 0.02 percent but the
Hang Seng IT Portfolio Index declined by 0.25 percent.
</P>
<P>
The HSI opened 6.8, or 0.04 percent, higher at 16,131.77
Tuesday and closed the morning session at 16,147.63. 
