<HEADLINE> Macao Airport Sees Booming Traffic in First Half Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Both passenger and cargo traffic at
the Macao International Airport rose considerably in the first
half of this year, according to a press release issued by the
airport Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The airport handled more than 1.53 million passengers in the
first six months of this year, an increase of 22 percent over the
same period of 1999.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the airport handled 30,613 tons of cargo and the
figure represents a 22-percent jump over a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
In June, both passenger and cargo traffic increased, by 17
percent and 77 percent respectively, over the same month of 1999.
And the number of plane landings and takeoffs also rose by 25
percent. 
</P>
