<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Mixed on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Share prices closed mixed on the
Singapore Stock Market Tuesday as the local bourse became
directionless because of Wall Street's closure for the U.S.
Independence Day holiday.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) inched down 1.61 points
to close at 2,072.42 in moderate trading.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume shrank to 476.51 million units worth
495.31 million Singapore dollars (285.86 million U.S. dollars).
There were 167 gainers against 142 losers with 238 counters
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Achieva was the most active stock with a turnover of 35.52
million units. It was followed by Ionics which had 28.53 million
shares done. AddvalTech was the next with 23.02 million counters
changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Venture headed the ascent of the day rising by 70 cents to
close at 18.7 Singapore dollars. NatEle moved up 30 cents to
finish at 5.5 Singapore dollars and DBS 20 cents to end at 23.3
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Creative 50 clinched the top position on the losers' list,
suffering a loss of 80 cents to close at 40.2 Singapore dollars.
PacCent gave up 70 cents to finish at 23.4 Singapore dollars while
SPH 100 shed 40 cents to end at 27.2 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers noted that investors searched for fresh trading
incentives as Tuesday night's closure of U.S. markets for the U.S.
Independence Day holiday caused directionless trading. 
</P>
</TEXT>
