<HEADLINE> Britain Remains Tanzania's Major Trading Partner </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Britain remains one of the
major trading partners of Tanzania with the volume of bilateral
trade totaling 80 million pounds (121 million U.S. dollars) last
year.
</P>
<P>
The Guardian newspaper Tuesday quoted British High Commissioner
in Dar es Salaam Bruce Dinwiddy as saying that he was pleased to
note that Britain' s visible exports to Tanzania stood at around
64 million pounds (97 million dollars) in 1999 and it was his hope
that bilateral trade would continue to grow.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a launching ceremony of the "Trade Partners UK"
web-site during the 24th Dar es Salaam International Trade Fair on
Monday, the British envoy expressed the belief that with
Tanzania's booming gold mining industry, its exports to Britain
will help narrow the trade gap between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The British government has set up "Trade Partners UK" web-site
to provide better services to its exporters and investors. It
offers access to its exporters' database containing details of
over 55,000 companies who wish to develop overseas trading links.
</P>
</TEXT>
