<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tajik President Hosts Banquet to Welcome China's Jiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DUSHANBE, Tajikistan, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Tajik President
Emomali Rakhmonov on Tuesday hosted a state banquet in honor of
Chinese President Jiang Zemin. The two heads of state highly
praised the development of bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who is on his first visit to this Central Asian country,
said in his speech that China was delighted to see that under the
leadership of President Rakhmonov, Tajikistan realized national
reconciliation and social stability with its own wisdom and
strength.
</P>
<P>
The country also scored achievements in economic recovery and
development, he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang highly commended the smooth development of friendly and
cooperative relations between the two countries after the
establishment of diplomatic ties eight years ago. The two peoples
are having increasingly frequent exchanges which help deepen
mutual understanding and trust, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president said China is willing to make concerted
efforts with Tajikistan to further consolidate and develop Sino-
Tajik ties in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Rakhmonov said in his speech that Jiang's state visit is "an
extraordinary major event" in the history of Sino-Tajik good-
neighborly and mutually beneficial cooperation.
</P>
<P>
After reviewing the trade and cultural links between the two
countries in the past 2,000 years, in particular in the thriving
period of the Silk Road, Rakhmonov said his country sincerely
hoped that such links would never be cut again, but would grow
steadily in the future.
</P>
<P>
The Tajik president also expressed his gratitude for the
political support given by China during the difficult days of
Tajikistan.
</P>
<P>
Tajikistan is determined to deepen mutually beneficial and good-
neighborly relations with China, he said, adding that such efforts
are "in the interests of our state and conductive to stability in
the region." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
