<HEADLINE> Shanghai B-share Market Edges Up at Tuesday Close </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai B-share market index
rose 0.24 points or 0.44 percent to the intraday high of 55.06
points at Tuesday's close.
</P>
<P>
The total turnover stood at 7.08 million U.S. dollars compared
with 10.02 million U.S. dollars on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The market struggled for most of the session on the negative
territory, but some bargain-hunters came to the rescue in the late
afternoon trading, pushing the index into the positive side,
according to Homeway, China's leading on-line financial and
securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
Both volume and volatility were on the fall with limited
participation, and the lackluster trading was confined to a very
narrow range of barely a half point, Homeway analysts said.
</P>
<P>
Advancing shares outnumbered declining shares by 26 to 8, with
other 20 unchanged.
</P>
<P>
On the winner's list, Shanghai Huili rose 8.13 percent to reach
0.266 U.S. dollars, while Wing Sung went up 2.88 percent to hit 0.
286 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Among losers, Goods &AMP; Materials lost 1.68 percent to 0.234 U.S.
dollars, while P&AMP;T Equipment fell 1.2 percent to 0.328 U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The recent market advance has met with underlying pressures as
investors were waiting anxiously for companies' release of the
interim reports, but it can chisel out minor gains in this
cautious sentiment, Homeway analysts said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
