<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese T-bond Trade Remains Narrow on Tuesday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The overall Chinese T-bond trade
stayed narrow today as the several stock subscriptions still "
locked" a considerable sum of money.
</P>
<P>
The trading volume on the market totaled 1.59 billion yuan, up
367 million yuan in comparison with the extremely sluggish trade
on Monday, according to Homeway, China's leading on-line financial
and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
Of the six outstanding treasuries, three advanced while three
declined. Bond 009704 recouped some losses with a jump of 0.54
percent, pressing the yield down 0.10 percentage point to 4.01
percent.
</P>
<P>
However, the turnover on the bond contracted from 255 million
yuan to 87 million yuan, suggesting that it is difficult for the
bond to go up too far.
</P>
<P>
The 10-year 010004 rallied slightly by 0.15 percent to close at
101.55 yuan with the yield stable at 2.70 percent. With the
biggest turnover of 695 million yuan, it is still the most active
performer on the T-bond market.
</P>
<P>
As the stock market had moved flatly with shrinking turnovers
for a long while before this week, the market sentiments on stocks
are not high at present in spite of the gain made by the stock
composite indices today.
</P>
<P>
Treasuries are expected to have a strong rally as the weakness
of domestic A shares may prompt a host of investors to seek safety
in government securities, Homeway analysts said.
</P>
<P>
China's repo market came down a lot following the sudden boom
on Monday. The trade volume on three-day, seven-day, 14-day, and
28-day transactions decreased by more than a half to 5.87 billion
yuan. However, the interest rate on the three-day transaction
climbed by 1.98 percentage points to 10 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
