<HEADLINE> Shenzhen B-share Market Edges up at Tuesday Close </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen B-share market index
gained 0.56 points or 0.50 percent to close at 112.31 points at
Tuesday close, fluctuating between 110.98 and 112.47.
</P>
<P>
The total turnover was 51.43 million HK dollars, slightly down
from 53.04 million HK dollars on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The market opened slightly lower today and soon headed
straightway to its intraday low due to lack of conviction for a
sure direction. Such sentiment lingered on throughout the session,
but buying interest increased in the last hour and picked up the
market, according to Homeway, China's leading on-line financial
and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
Rising shares outnumbered falling issues by 26 to 22, with
other 6 unchanged. Shares under the "Special Treatment" category
were actively traded but had a divergent path.
</P>
<P>
ST Pro &AMP; Res Dev rose to its price ceiling of 5.00 percent and
ended at 1.26 HK dollars, while ST China Bicycle and ST Lionda
Hold both fell about 5.3 percent to close at 1.07 HK dollars and 1.
43 HK dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
The recent market advance met with underlying pressure as
investor were anxiously awaiting companies' release of interim
reports, but it can chisel out minor gains in this cautious
sentiment, Homeway analysts said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
