<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Escaped Thief Caught at Court Hearing on His Own Case </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 4 (Xinhua) -- A daring thief was recently caught
in a local court in the Chinese capital, when he sat among the
audience of a court hearing on the very case he was involved,
Beijing Morning News reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
On June 29, the local court of Fengtai District, in southern
Beijing, held a hearing on two thieves, whose surnames were known
as Ma and Zhao. A total of three suspects, besides the caught two,
were involved in a series of stealing cases, according to the
public persecutor of the district.
</P>
<P>
Unexpectedly, Li, the third defendant of the case who went into
hiding and was still wanted by the police, was seated among the
audience. He was not discovered until one of his fellows sitting
beside accidentally called his name and asked for a key.
</P>
<P>
Upon hearing Li's name, the judges and the public persecutors
immediately verified him by reading the files and ordered the
police to check his ID card which betrayed his identity.
</P>
<P>
Ma and Zhao also confessed to the court that Li was their
companion in the case.
</P>
<P>
Nowadays, people are allowed to attend any open hearing held by
local courts in China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
