<DOCNO> XIE20000704.0176 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israel's Direct Overseas Investment Soars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Direct overseas investment of
Israeli companies (excluding banks) soared by 1.1 billion U.S.
dollars in the first four months of this year, Israel's Ha'aretz
daily reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
This indeed meant a drastic increase as compared to an average
annual rise of 600 million dollars in the last five years.
</P>
<P>
As of the end of April, Israel's direct overseas investment
totaled 6.4 billion dollars, over 90 percent of which went to North
America, with 3 billion dollars, and Western Europe, with 2.8
billion dollars, according to Bank of Israel's data.
</P>
<P>
Most of the investments were in the fields of electronics and
telecommunication.
</P>
<P>
Some 56 percent of Israeli investments were conducted via share
exchanges rather than cash.
</P>
<P>
Israelis' direct overseas investment in overseas real estate was
only 45 million dollars in the January-April period, compared to
367 million dollars in all of 1999 and 220 million dollars in 1998,
the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
