<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand, Laos Re-Open Checkpoint Along Border </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The Chong Mek checkpoint along the
Thai-Lao border in Sirindhorn district of Thailand's northeastern
province of Ubon Rachathani has been re-opened following clashes
between Laotian troops and armed dissidents, the Thai News Agency
(TNA) reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Chong Mek checkpoint was re-opened for cross-border
travelling and trade, hours after the incident on Monday, which
caused five deaths and several injuries, said the report.
</P>
<P>
More than 25 members of the so-called White Lao Force are now
detained at the Chong Mek police station after escaping into Thai
territory, it added.
</P>
<P>
The armed dissidents stormed a local customs and immigration
checkpoint, known as the Wang Tao Checkpoint across Sirindhorn
district, at around 03:00 a.m. on Monday. After a 20-minute clash
with officers at the checkpoint, the dissidents seized the customs
station.
</P>
<P>
However, they surrendered to government troops at around 08:00
a.m.
</P>
<P>
More Thai security officers have been deployed with increased
surveillance following the incident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
