<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Broadly Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed broadly higher Tuesday on technical
rebound, but trading remained thin.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index rose 13.94
points or 1.76 percent to 807.87, the all-share Emas Index added 2.
92 points to 202.4, the Industrial Index gained 20.46 points to 1,
402.39 and the Second Board Index rose 1.56 points to 213.3.
</P>
<P>
Gainers led losers by 444 to 146 while 141 counters were
unchanged and 258 others untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover declined to 79.794 million shares worth 305.
73 million ringgit (80.45 million U.S. dollars) from 89.466
million shares valued at 361.879 million ringgit (95.23 million
dollars) on Monday. 
</P>
