<DOCNO> XIE20000704.0184 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Woman Injuring Girl with Nitric Acid Sentenced to Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, July 4 (Xinhua) -- A woman who used nitric acid to
burn the face of a 14-year-old girl has been sentenced to death in
this north China port city.
</P>
<P>
Liu Jinfeng married Zhang Jianhuan in 1994. In 1998, Zhang
migrated to Canada and asked for divorce with Liu. Liu felt she
was hurt.
</P>
<P>
To revenge Zhang, she called on Zhang Shuai, the daughter of
Zhang's elder brother, on May 29 of this year. Liu poured a bottle
of nitric acid she carried with her on Zhang's head while they
were chatting.
</P>
<P>
Zhang's forehead, face, eyes and neck were heavily burnt. Liu
was then arrested by the police.
</P>
<P>
Doctors ruled out the possibility that Liu suffered from lunacy.
</P>
</TEXT>
