<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shenzhen A-share Market Rebounds at Tuesday Close </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen composite index closed
at 596.7 points on Tuesday, up 5.66 points from the last close.
The sub-index closed at 4753.47 points, 14.11 points higher than
that of yesterday morning.
</P>
<P>
The turnover hit 9.6 billion yuan (1.16 billion U.S. dollars),
20.66 percent less than yesterday's 12.1 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The Shenzhen composite index had a sharp rebound and closed at
a high level, but followed by little trading. The highly-expected
companies led the market up, according to Homeway, China's leading
on-line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
The market expansion pressure led the two stock markets down
yesterday. Five companies issued new shares on the two bourses,
and eight transferred rights shares with a market value of 4.04
billion yuan were listed on the Shanghai Stock Exchange at the
same time.
</P>
<P>
Investors were still concerned about companies' interim reports
and issuance of new stocks, Homeway analysts said.
</P>
<P>
Xiangyang Automobile Bearing Share Co. Ltd. and Chengdu Yinhe
Power Co. Ltd. were the top gainers today with their prices up 10
percent to the ceiling.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen Lionda Holdings Co. Ltd., a ST company, was the
biggest loser today. Its price dropped 5.05 percent to the floor
to 8.08 yuan per share.
</P>
<P>
The market is likely to test 600 points tomorrow, Homeway
analysts predicted.  
</P>
</TEXT>
