<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Manila Stocks End Slightly Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Share prices in the Philippine Stock
Exchange ended slightly higher Tuesday despite absence of fresh
positive news to spur market activity.
</P>
<P>
The 30-company Phisix, the market's main index, rose 3.23
points to close at 1,538.88. The broader all-shares also gained
marginally by 0.61 of a point to 656.33.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that despite the slight gain, the market still
remained dim as investors currently lacked interest in trading.
</P>
<P>
Turnover rose to 1.9 billion shares worth some 13 million U.S.
dollars on Tuesday compared with 783 million shares worth some 10
million dollars on Monday.
</P>
<P>
In Tuesday's trading, losers beat gainers 57 to 29 while 42
shares remained unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000704.0199 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian Leader Urges Efforts to Restore Confidence in Rupiah </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President Abdurrahman
Wahid Tuesday asked all parties in the country to help the
government in its efforts to restore confidence in the rupiah, the
country's currency.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters at the Presidential Palace here, Wahid
said:"The government cannot do that alone."
</P>
<P>
He added that the government has implemented the country's
economic reform programs outlined in the letter of intent signed
between the government and the International Monetary Fund.
</P>
<P>
"Ministers have done their best and have hammered it out," the
president said.
</P>
<P>
But the rupiah seems to keep dropping further to a lower level,
as it traded at 8,875 (buying) and 9,025 (selling) per U.S. dollar
on Tuesday morning, or significantly down from last weekend's 8,
650 (buying) and 8,800 (selling) for one U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
Separately, Finance Minister Bambang Sudibyo reiterated that
the continuing fall of the rupiah is largely caused by non-
economic factors but he hoped the currency will soon regain
strength.
</P>
<P>
"Ideally, the exchange rate of the rupiah stands at the level
of 6,000 to 7,000 per U.S. dollar," Sudibyo told reporters in the
parliament building here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The government set the exchange rate of the rupiah at 7,000 per
dollar in the current state budget. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
