<DOCNO> XIE20000704.0200 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kenya Gets Loan From European Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Kenya had been granted loans
totalling 171. 81 million euros (163 million U.S. dollars) for 11
projects from the European Investment Bank (EIB), according to the
bank's annual report.
</P>
<P>
Kenya became one of the main destinations for EIB loans in
sub-Saharan Africa in 1999, the Daily Nation newspaper reported
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In east Africa, Uganda received 18.363 million euros (17.43
million dollars) last year and Tanzania got 9 million euros (8.5
million dollars), the annual report said.
</P>
<P>
Among the loans to Kenya's 11 projects, a 41-million-euro loan
went to the Kenya Electricity Generation Company for the
construction of a new geothermal power station with transmission
lines and substations in the capital Nairobi.
</P>
<P>
Another 9 million euros will be used to construct a new steel
galvanizing line at the Mabati Rolling Mill in Mariakani, Mombasa,
an Indian Ocean port city in southeastern Kenya. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
