<DOCNO> XIE20000704.0201 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Begins Disbursement of AIDS Trust Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The long-awaited disbursement of
money from Zimbabwe's National AIDS Trust, set up to alleviate
suffering caused by the killer disease, has started with 20
organizations expected to receive 1.3 million U.S. dollars by the
end of the month.
</P>
<P>
The National AIDS Council Board of Trustees approved the budget
at its meeting Monday.
</P>
<P>
At least 13 million dollars is now in the fund's coffers. Of
the money, more than 7.8 million dollars was collected by the
government as four months' AIDS Levy, while the remainder is
interest earned from investing the money.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe is currently ranked the second country worst affected
by HIV/ AIDS in the world. About a quarter of the country's
population is HIV/AIDS positive and more than 1,500 people are
dying of the disease every week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
