<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Mixed in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices closed mixed in Tokyo
Tuesday, with the benchmark Nikkei index turning downward
following previous gains.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange lost 144.51 points, or 0.82
percent from Monday's close to end at 17,470.15.
</P>
<P>
In contrast, the Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, added 3.43 points or 0.21 percent to 1,606.
94.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section decreased to 841.84 million
shares from Monday's 1,017.11 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Nippon Steel was the day's volume leader.
</P>
<P>
Traders said the key market gauge was dampened by drops in
several high-tech issues which heavily affect the movement of the
Nikkei index.
</P>
<P>
High-priced information and telecom issues were mixed, while
non-bank moneylenders, the mining, textile and real estate sectors
were lower.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, losers outpaced
gainers 696 to 593, with 115 issues closing unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
