<HEADLINE> China Sets up First Joint-stock Gold Firm </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The first share-holding gold
company in China has been set up in the bonded zone in this north
China port city.
</P>
<P>
The China Gold Corporation has a dominant stake of 84 percent
in the company, while the other six corporate share-holders hold
the rest 16 percent shares.
</P>
<P>
With a registered capital of 180 million yuan and net assets of
275 million yuan, the company is expected to handle 2080 tons of
gold-ore daily and realize more than 50 million yuan in profit
this year.
</P>
<P>
The company is now building a new production line aimed at
producing refined gold products to better cater to international
as well as domestic need. To raise more funds, the company is
applying for public offering. 
</P>
