<HEADLINE> Hi-tech Zones Promote Economic Growth in E. China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANTAI, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The ten major new and high tech
development zones in east China's Shandong Province have become a
driving force behind local economic growth.
</P>
<P>
The ten zones currently have more than 10,000 enterprises,
turning out 5.5 billion yuan in taxes and profits last year,
government officials said.
</P>
<P>
In the port city of Qingdao, new and high tech zones contribute
15 percent to the city's gross domestic product.
</P>
<P>
Exports from new and high tech zones in Weihai accounted for a
quarter of the coastal city's total.
</P>
<P>
Shandong started building new and high tech development zones
in Yantai, Qingdao, Weihai and other cities 10 years ago.
</P>
<P>
To date, the zones have attracted more than 10,000 talented
people and made a number of inventions.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, foreign investors have come to invest in more than 1,
000 projects with exports surpassing 700 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
More than 400 business incubators have been set up, after the
management committees of the zones began to carry out co-operation
with more than 200 Chinese and foreign colleges and research
institutions, the officials said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
