<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Colored Cotton Growing Well in Xinjiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, July 4 (Xinhua) -- More than 4,000 hectares of colored
cotton in northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region have
survived a series of strong sand storms and hail storms this year
and are growing very well.
</P>
<P>
Professor Zhang Zhennan from the colored cotton production base
said that a bumper harvest of the colored cotton is expected if
there is no further harmful disasters.
</P>
<P>
Colored cotton is pollution-free, involving no bleaching and
dying and sold two or three times higher than the price of
ordinary cotton.
</P>
<P>
Tiancai Science and Technology Stock Company started
experiments with growing colored cotton at the Awat County and the
city of Shihezi in 1994. At present, brown green and light tan
cottons are available on the local market.
</P>
<P>
Xinjiang, China's leading cotton grower, plans to expand the
region's acreage of colored cotton to 33,333 hectares soon.
</P>
<P>
The company has developed a long-fibre cotton ranging from 35
to 37 mm in length and new cotton strains which resist cotton
aphids and other diseases. The company's output value of colored
cotton surpassed 100 million yuan last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
