<HEADLINE> Shanghai A-share Market Rebounds at Tuesday Close </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai composite index closed
at 1907.93 points Tuesday, up 12.3 points from last close.
</P>
<P>
The total trading volume was 9.4 billion yuan (1.13 billion U.S.
dollars), down 21 percent from the previous session's 11.9 billion.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai composite index witnessed a sharp rebound and
closed high, but followed by little trading. Fast-growing
companies led the market up, according to Homeway, China's leading
on-line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
Market expansion pressure led the market down Monday. Five
companies issued new shares on the two bourses in Shanghai and
Shenzhen, and eight transferred rights shares with a market value
of 4.04 billion yuan were listed on the Shanghai Stock Exchange at
the same time.
</P>
<P>
Investors were still concerned over the listed companies'
interim earnings reports and issuance of new stocks, Homeway
analysts said.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Medical Equipment Co., Ltd. was the top gainer in
Tuesday's trading, with its price rising 9.99 percent to the
ceiling of 19.26 yuan per share.
</P>
<P>
Shouchuang Tech, formerly known as Ningbo Zhongbai Co., Ltd.,
was the biggest loser Tuesday, with its price dropping 6.32
percent to hit 17.18 yuan per share.
</P>
<P>
The market is likely to test the supporting line at the 1900-
point level Wednesday, analysts predicted.  
</P>
</TEXT>
