<HEADLINE> FM Spokesman: Allegation of China's Assistance in Pakistan's Missile Program Groundless </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The allegation that China has
assisted Pakistan in its long-range missile program is totally
groundless and relevant reports are out of ulterior motives, said
Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Sun Yuxi here today.
</P>
<P>
Sun stressed at a regular press conference this afternoon that
China has always abided by the joint communique of foreign
ministers of the five permanent members of the United Nations (UN)
Security Council issued in June 1998 concerning nuclear tests in
south Asia, and also the UN No. 1172 resolution.
</P>
<P>
China will not help south Asian nations develop nuclear weapons
or ballistic missiles to be used in carrying nuclear weapons, he
said. 
</P>
