<HEADLINE> China Respects Any Decision Favoring Middle East Peace Process: FM Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman
Sun Yuxi said today that China has always been supportive to
Palestine's just cause and respected any decision made by
Palestine that favors the peace process in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
Sun said this at the regular press conference this afternoon in
response to a question on Palestine's recent announcement to
declare an independent state in September.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian issue is at the core of the Middle East issue,
he said.
</P>
<P>
China established diplomatic ties with Palestine as early as
1998, therefore China supports the Palestinian people to recover
their legitimate rights, including the rights of going back to
their homes and establishing an independent state.
</P>
<P>
This is also the obligation of the international community, Sun
noted.
</P>
<P>
China hopes that Palestine and Israel will abide by all
agreements already reached, and solve the issue regarding the
final status of Palestine through flexible and pragmatic
negotiations, he added. 
</P>
