Police spokesman Chief Superintendent Wayne Bvudzijena said
Monday the special units were deployed following spates of violent
clashes between supporters of the opposition Movement for
Democratic Change (MDC) and the ruling Zimbabwe African National
Union-Patriotic Front (Zanu-pf).
</P>
<P>
He said the police were deployed in areas where there was a
risk of a political flare-up.
</P>
<P>
