patrols to maintain a peaceful situation and stop acts of
political violence from generating into worse situations," he
said.
</P>
<P>
He also dismissed reports that the police used excessive force
in some of the troubled spots, saying they acted within their
parameters to restore calm and peace.
</P>
<P>
About 30 people have been arrested for the post-electoral
violence in Harare and Kwekwe since Wednesday last week.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Chairman of the War Veterans Association Chenjerai
Hunzvi said his members were ready to counter any action by the
MDC and white commercial farmers and they would stay on the farms
they occupied until the land is equitably redistributed.
</P>
<P>
He warned the MDC and the white commercial farmers that if they
had any plans to drive war veterans away, they should abandon
them.
</P>
<P>
