<HEADLINE> Indonesia Badminton Open to be Held in Jakarta </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Twenty countries and regions,
including China and South Korea, have confirmed their
participation in the Sanyo Indonesia Open Badminton Championships
to be held here from July 19 to 23.
</P>
<P>
Secretary-general of the Badminton Association of Indonesia (
PBSI) Chandra Wiranata said that the number of participating
countries had grown significantly compared to last year's
tournament.
</P>
<P>
"This year's tournament is much better compared to last year's
in Bali. China has skipped the Indonesia Open three times in a row
while (South) Korea has missed twice. Their participation will be
an added value to the tournament," he was quoted by the Jakarta
Post Tuesday as saying.
</P>
<P>
Other participants are Denmark, Sweden, England, the
Netherlands, France, Wales, Switzerland, the United States, the
Czech Republic, Bulgaria, Italy, Germany, Japan, Hong Kong,
Singapore, India and Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Indonesia won the men's singles, women's singles,
men's doubles and mixed doubles, leaving the women's doubles title
to Denmark. 
