<HEADLINE> Tianjin, Taiwan Students in Cultural Camp </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, July 4 (Xinhua) -- More than 100 students from Tianjin
and Taiwan Monday started a week-long camping activity for
cultural exchanges.
</P>
<P>
The Taiwan students, including those from colleges, middle and
primary schools, will be able to visit the Great Wall, the Palace
Museum, the Temple of Heaven and the Summer Palace in Beijing,
and watch folk art performances and listen to lectures on ballad
singing, story telling, comic dialogues, clapper talks, and cross
talks in Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
These students will also visit families of Tianjin students.
</P>
<P>
Qu Gengshen, director of Tianjin Office of the Taiwan Affairs,
noted that it is of significance for students from Taiwan to trace
after their root and learn about the Chinese culture during the
week-long gala.
</P>
<P>
Wang Yonghai, vice-director of the Taiwan Affairs Office of the
State Council, quoted President Jiang Zemin as saying that the 5,
000-year-old Chinese civilization would always serve as a
spiritual link for the whole Chinese nation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
