<HEADLINE> China Builds Asia's Largest Underground Copper Mine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, July 4 (Xinhua) -- China has completed an 899-meter-deep
shaft at the Dongguashan copper mine in east China's Anhui
Province after ten years of construction.
</P>
<P>
The shaft is so far the deepest in the country.
</P>
<P>
The mine has 92.9 million tons of copper ore reserves and the
ore is of good quality.
</P>
<P>
The Tongling Non-ferrous Group Co. in Anhui has started to work
on the shaft since May 1990. 
