<HEADLINE> Economic News Briefs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Today's economic news briefs:
</P>
<P>
Sichuan Reports Increasing Exports
</P>
<P>
Southwest China's Sichuan Province recorded a total export and
import volume of 965 million U.S. dollars in the first five months
this year, according to the Chengdu Customs.
</P>
<P>
Imports valued at 548 million U.S. dollars in the period, an
increase of 19 percent over the corresponding period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Asia remains the top export market of this southwest China
province, with the export volume totaling 391 million U.S. dollars,
a 22.7 increase over last year's same period. Exports to the
European market climbed up by 13.2 percent to 68.04 million U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan Improves Investment Environment
</P>
<P>
Sichuan Province has adopted a series of measures to improve
its investment environment to lure more foreign funds.
</P>
<P>
This measures include preferential policies on taxation, use of
land, procedures for approving investment projects and investment
safety. The province has revoked 54 out-of-date documents to clear
way for the inflow of investment from both at home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan signed 98 contracts, involving 13.7 billion yuan (165
million U.S. dollars), on investment projects with other provinces
of the country during a recent trade fair for enterprises from
coastal areas.
</P>
<P>
The province approved 106 overseas-funded enterprises in the
January-May period this year, up 34.18 from last year's same
period. Contracted foreign investment totaled 298 million U.S.
dollars, an increase of 16.86 percent.
</P>
<P>
 Tibet's Insurance Industry Develops Rapidly
</P>
<P>
The insurance industry has developed rapidly in the Tibet
Autonomous Region since the late 1980s.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the Tibet branch of the People's Insurance
Company of China had recorded a total premium of 56.19 million
yuan (6.76 million U.S. dollars) by the end of 1999.
</P>
<P>
The branch now handles 68 kinds of insurance covering vehicles,
enterprises, property and cargo transportation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
