<HEADLINE> Three Illegal CD Production Lines Closed Down in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Economic and police authorities of
the Macao Special Administrative Region (SAR) government made
joint efforts to close down three production lines making pirated
optical compact disks.
</P>
<P>
In a factory, inspectors detected five CD identification codes
which coincided with some codes printed on pirated CDs, the Macao
Daily News reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
With the aim of distinguishing products from different
manufacturers, one CD-making company normally is given only one CD
identification code.
</P>
<P>
The three production lines, worth 12 million patacas (about 1.5
million U.S. dollars), was the biggest piracy case cracked by the
local authorities.
</P>
<P>
The Macao SAR government has exerted more efforts this year to
protect intellectual property rights and was moved from the U.S. "
Priority Watch List" to the "Watch List" in May. 
</P>
</TEXT>
