<HEADLINE> Yugoslavia Determined to Protect National Sovereignty, Says FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, July 3 (Xinhua) -- National unity, self-reliance and
strengthened cooperation with the outside world are the important
factors that guarantee the victory in the Yugoslav fight for
national sovereignty and reconstruction, said Foreign Minister
Zivadin Jovanovic Monday.
</P>
<P>
Jovanovic was speaking at a ceremony for a major highway bridge
to open to traffic. The bridge, connecting Belgrade and the Nish
highway, was destroyed during NATO's 78-day air strikes against
Yugoslavia last year.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the bridge is a monument of victories for
builders over destroyers, civilization over brutality, and
humanism over barbarism.
</P>
<P>
With the bridge open to traffic, all the bridges in Yugoslavia
connecting with European Expressway 75, that had been destroyed
during NATO bombings, had been rebuilt, he said.
</P>
<P>
Jovanovic also said that Yugoslavia will continue to pursue a
foreign policy of peace and cooperation. It will firmly protect
national sovereignty and territorial integrity, rebuild the
homeland and continue the reforms.
</P>
<P>
Hegemonism and power politics are not in line with the
interests of the people in the Balkans, and only exchanges and
cooperation will contribute to peace and stability in Europe,
Jovanovic said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
