<HEADLINE> Factory Explosion Kills One in SW China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, July 4 (Xinhua) -- An explosion which occurred around
19:50 on Monday evening at a factory at Dafeng Town, Xindu County
in southwest China's Sichuan Province, killed at least one person
and injured a number of others.
</P>
<P>
A report reaching here Tuesday quoted local fire-fighting
police as saying the impulsion from the blast at the Tiansheng
Packaging Materials Co., Ltd. threw a number of cans containing
butane out of the firm's workshop, and glasses of buildings nearby
were broken into pieces.
</P>
<P>
A fire that erupted in the three-story workshop following the
explosion was extinguished two hours later and a charred body was
found at the scene, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Initial investigation indicates that the blast was caused by
two cans containing several hundred kg of butane.
</P>
<P>
The accident is under further investigation. 
</P>
