women to be managers each year and help them run enterprises so
that more laid-off women can be re-employed.
</P>
<P>
She said laid-off women in the city now have gradually gotten
rid of their dependence on large enterprises and State-owned
institutions to find new jobs.
</P>
<P>
"Many are beginning to look for jobs at job centers," Meng said.
</P>
<P>
