<HEADLINE> Czech ATP Tournament Cancelled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PRAGUE, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The ATP tennis tournament scheduled
for Prague in September has been cancelled for financial reasons,
Czech sports papers reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Czech Tennis Assosiation (CTS) failed to raise the ATP's
minimum
financial guarantee before the June 30 deadline. The ATP also
refused to sell the tournament to another city.
</P>
<P>
Initially scheduled for May 1-7, the 400,000 dollar tournament
had already switched dates and was replacing the Mallorca Open
from September 11-17.
</P>
<P>
The first Prague tournament took place in 1987 at the Stvanice
Stadium in August 1987. 
</P>
</TEXT>
