<HEADLINE> Middlesbrough Silent on "Absent" Gascoigne Talk </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Middlesbrough are remaining tight-
lipped over claims that troubled midfielder Paul Gascoigne failed
to turn up for a cards-on-the-table meeting to discuss his future
on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Boro declined to comment on reports that the 33-year-old former
England star did not keep an appointment with manager Bryan Robson,
chief executive Keith Lamb and agent Mel Stein, but it is
understood that was the case.
</P>
<P>
The incident is bound to spark further speculation over
Gascoigne's career, and he is once again being linked with a move
to Australia.
</P>
<P>
He still has a year left on his contract at the Riverside
Stadium, but he has played so little football in recent times that
the time may have come when even Robson, for so long such a
staunch supporter of the errant genius, could be persuaded that
things have come to a head.
</P>
<P>
The manager is close to concluding deals for midfield duo
Christian Karembeu, an unused substitute as France added the Euro
2000 crown to the World Cup triumph in Rotterdam on Sunday night,
and Australian Paul Okon, and with Paul Ince and Christian Ziege
already assured of places, the clock is ticking on Gascoigne.
</P>
