<HEADLINE> 13 Killed, Six Badly Injured in Guangdong Bus Plunge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Thirteen people have been killed,
six severely injured and one missing, as a mini-bus carrying 20
people plunged off a road and fell 600 feet (200 meters) into a
ravine in south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred Saturday night in Ruyuan County, Shaoguan
city, when the rental bus with workers of the Huanggang Steel
Works was heading for a nearby ravine scenic spot.
</P>
<P>
The bus veered off a narrow mountain path at a sharp turn,
which is considered as the most dangerous road section in the
ravine area.
</P>
<P>
Local people soon rushed to rescue, while some 60 workers used
knives and axes to cut a road through the dense forest in the
hilly area and sent six badly-injured survivors to hospital.
</P>
<P>
The injured now have no life danger in hospital, and the rescue
team are still searching for the missing one.  
</P>
</TEXT>
