<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Economic News Briefs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Today's economic news briefs:
</P>
<P>
 Pitch Production Line
</P>
<P>
A pitch production line with an annual output of 350,000 tons,
the largest of its kind in China, went into operation recently at
the Xi'an Petrol-chemical Works in northwest China. It will
alleviate China's dependence on imports of high-grade pitch.
</P>
<P>
Color TV Tube Enterprise Founded
</P>
<P>
The Ancai Electronic Glass Corp. Ltd. was set up recently in
Chengdu, capital of southwest China's Sichuan Province. It will
produce glass tubes for color TV from 15 to 21 inches with a
designed output value of 1 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Investment Projects
</P>
<P>
Lhasa, capital of southwest China's Tibet Autonomous Region,
provides Chinese and foreign investors with 36 projects in water,
power and mineral exploitation, agriculture and tourism, which
need 2.1 billion yuan of investment.
</P>
<P>
Artificial Rain
</P>
<P>
Southwest China's Sichuan Province effectively alleviated a
severe drought by carrying out artificial rain operation. The
province has sent 15 cloud-seeding helicopters and brought about
one billion cubic meters of rainfall for 100 counties.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that 1.5 million hectares of farmland in 90
counties were affected by drought this year.
</P>
<P>
More Tourists to Ningxia
</P>
<P>
More than 240,000 tourists from the United State, Japan,
Singapore and Europe visited scenic spots in northwest China's
Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region so far this year, 140 percent more
than last year's same period. Major parks in Ningxia gained 6
million yuan and 200,000 U.S. dollars of tourism income. 
</P>
</TEXT>
