<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Philippine Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in the leading Philippine newspapers Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Manila Bulletin:
</P>
<P>
-- Philippine President Joseph Estrada reiterated Monday that
the Moro Islamic Liberation Front must abandon its demand for
independent state and stop all terrorist acts in return for a one-
week ceasefire to bring back peace to Central Mindanao.
</P>
<P>
Philippine Daily Inquirer:
</P>
<P>
-- Philippine Defense Secretary Orlando Mercado admitted Monday
that the military had been attacking the past few days Camp
Abubakar, the headquarters of the Moro Islamic Liberation Front
and the last remaining stronghold of the rebel group.
</P>
<P>
The Manila Times:
</P>
<P>
-- The United States and Philippine government are set to sign
an agreement for the clean up of "hazardous waste," although
Washington still refuses to acknowledge responsibility for toxic
wastes in its former military bases in the Philippines. 
</P>
</TEXT>
