<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0030 GMT, July 4 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA -- The Palestine Liberation Organization (PLO) Central
Council approved on Monday the plan to declare an independent
state on September 13 this year. The 129-member PLO Central
Council, on its second day of meetings in the Gaza Strip,
supported Arafat's plan to declare a state in the West Bank and
Gaza even if a final peace could not be reached with Israel, said
a council statement. (Palestine-Statehood)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan on Monday
sent a reconnaissance mission to Eritrea and Ethiopia to discuss
possible U.N. assistance in facilitating the implementation of a
cease-fire agreement between the two countries.  (UN-Annan-
Eritrea-Ethiopia)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PARIS -- French President Jacques Chirac said Monday that the
European Union (EU) sanctions against Austria will stay in force
until the three experts designated by the European Court of Human
Rights submit their report on the situation of refugees,
immigrants and minority groups in Austria. (France-EU-Austria)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BERLIN -- Germany and the European Union (EU) both said Monday
that they will do everything to win freedom for the 20 Western and
Asian hostages who have been held by Philippine Islamic extremists
for over two months. (Germany-EU-Hostages) 
</P>
</TEXT>
