<DOCNO> XIE20000704.0315 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Smuggled Goods Seized in Guangdong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHUHAI, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The Gongbei Customs in south China's
Guangdong Province have seized smuggled goods worth 63.2 million
yuan (7.5 million U.S. dollars) in the first half of this year,
sources said.
</P>
<P>
Some 214 cases have been investigated by customs officers in
the coastal city of Zhuhai, which is adjacent to Macao.
</P>
<P>
The recent big cases include the smuggling of 2.5-million-yuan-
worth cars in eight containers on June 27, and the shipping of
some high-tech products.
</P>
<P>
China has intensified anti-smuggling campaign this year.
Smuggling is usually rampant in Guangdong and other southern
coastal regions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
