<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Algerian President Pardons Prisoners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Under the amnesty decree, 4,000 prisoners will be set free, the
Algerian News Agency quoted a presidential statement as saying.
</P>
<P>
The decree is part of the general endeavor to build a state of
law. It is also part of the measures adopted by Bouteflika since he
took office on April 27, 1999 and the measures on improvement of
prison conditions, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The amnesty decree includes neither the security prisoners nor
the persons who were convicted on serious crimes such as murder,
rape and drug trafficking, according to the statement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
