<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brasil's Trade Surplus to Reach 1.1 Billion Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's trade surplus will reach
1.1 billion dollars, less than the government's preliminary target
of 2.8 billion dollars, said the National Industry Confederation (
NIC) on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
 The organization forecasted that the South American country's
exports will be 54.3 billion dollars, increasing 13 percent over
1999; imports will be 53.2 billion dollars, 8 percent over last
year.
</P>
<P>
 The gross domestic product (GDP) will increase by 4 percent,
mainly estimated by the industrial sector, which will grow 6
percent this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
