<DOCNO> XIE20000704.0324 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Argentine Stocks Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The leading Merval index on
the Buenos Aires Exchange Tuesday closed up 1.27 percent at 520.
44 points compared with Monday's 513.90 points.
</P>
<P>
The turnover fell sharply to only 15.879 million U.S. dollars
from 107.733 million U.S. dollars in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The annual inter-bank interest rate dropped to 7.40 percent
from 7.55 percent in the 24-hour term. The exchange rate of the
Argentine peso against the U.S. dollar stood at 0.997 for purchase
and 1.002 for sale. 
</P>
</TEXT>
