<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greeks Demonstrate in Protest Against Racial Discrimination </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ATHENS, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Thousands of Greeks later Tuesday
took to the streets of central Athens to show their opposition to
racial discrimination.
</P>
<P>
Holding banners and signs with slogans advocating a society
free of intolerance, the demonstrators began their march at the
Propylaia on central Panepistimiou street and ended in front of
the Greek Parliament.
</P>
<P>
They urged the Greek government to legalize all immigrants and
to stop the closed borders policy of the European Union (EU) and
the Schengen Treaty.
</P>
<P>
The anti-racism march was organized by the "Stop Haider
Initiative," the Athens Labor Center and the Civil Servants
Supreme Administrative Council as well as by anti-racist and
leftist organizations, such as the Left Coalition and the
Socialist Workers' Party of Greece (SEKE).
</P>
<P>
The demonstration is aimed at intensifying the fight against
racism and discrimination, not only against migrants and refugees,
but also of Greek minority group members. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
