<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Asbestos - A Bigger Killer Than Road Accidents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 4 (Xinhua) -- The number of work-related deaths
caused by asbestos in Britain is on the increase even though new
uses of the fiber have been banned,Unions warned Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Trade Union Confederation (TUC) said 4000 people die of
asbestos-related diseases every year - more than are killed on the
roads.
</P>
<P>
In 20 years, it will become the largest single cause of male
mortality under the age of 65, the TUC added.
</P>
</TEXT>
