<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Slovak Health Minister to Resign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Slovak health minister Tibor Sagat
has decided to resign from his post in a controversy over the
medical treatment of ailing President Rudolf Schuster, the Czech
News Agency quoted Slovak Prime Minister Mikulas Dzurinda as
saying Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Dzurinda said Sagat would formally hand in his resignation on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Slovak media have recently criticized Sagat for alleged
mismanagement of President's care and the bad state of the country
's health service.
</P>
<P>
Schuster, 66, underwent two "life-saving" emergency operations
to repair a perforated colon after he was hospitalized on June 14.
His condition deteriorated following complications after surgery.
Then Schuster was transferred to Austria to receive an emergency
treatment last Wednesday. According to the latest reports, his
condition began to stabilize, but still remains serious. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
