<HEADLINE> Over One Ton of Cocaine Seized from Colombian Paramilitary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Five men were held for smuggling the drug, found at a rural
zone in Yambo, close to Cali, over 530 kilometers away from
Colombia's capital.
</P>
<P>
National Police subdirector General Alfredo Salgado Mendes said
that, beside the drug, was found a war arsenal and garments with
badges of United Autodefenses of Colombia (AUC, which brings
together extreme-right groups).
</P>
<P>
Police from the region made the discovery during a register
that allowed them to find a hideaway of the paramilitary
association, which has widened in year 2000 its activity to the
country's southeast.
</P>
<P>
GeneraL Salgado explained that Police confiscated something
over 1,000 kilos of cocaine that had been prepared to be sent
abroad, as well as several rifles, grenades and ammunition.
</P>
