<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hungarian Passenger Plane Lands Successfully in Northern Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ATHENS, July 4 (Xinhua) -- A Hungarian plane carrying 76
passengers and crew later Tuesday landed successfully at the
northern Greek airport of Macedonia after it failed in its first
landing due to the problem of the landing system.
</P>
<P>
The plane, a Tupolev-type of Hungary's Malev Airlines, had
skidded for about 400 meters and its tail initially touched the
ground three times before the pilot managed to lift it up again
for the second landing, the semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA)
reported.
</P>
<P>
All passengers and crew were reported unharmed after the plane
on route from Budapest to the northern Greek city of Thessaloniki
landed successfully on a second attempt 15 minutes later. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
