<DOCNO> XIE20000704.0333 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mexican President-elect to Seek Investments </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Mexican President-elect Vicente
Fox said Tuesday he would travel abroad to seek more investments
for the country.
</P>
<P>
Fox said he would visit extensively in the next few months,
to seek improved ties with Mexico's partners and to promote
investments.
</P>
<P>
He is planning to visit the United States to meet President
Bill Clinton, he said, adding that he would also hold talks with
presidential candidates George W. Bush and Al Gore.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a news conference, he said he also planned to visit
Canada and several European and Latin American countries.
</P>
<P>
"Our interest is political ties, learning from (other countries
') experiences and the access and proximity to markets, to
investors and with trade," said Fox .
</P>
<P>
Fox expressed hope to strengthen the North American Free Trade
(NAFTA) agreement between Canada and the United States in order to
create a market similar to the European Common Market.
</P>
<P>
The 58-year old former rancher and Coca Cola regional
executive got 43 percent of the votes on Sunday's presidential
election, while Fransico Labastida, the candidate of the ruling
part, won 36 percent and Cuauhtemoc Cardenas, a leftist candidate,
won 17 percent. Fox will take office on December 1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
