<HEADLINE> UN Peacekeepers Retake Strategic Town in S.Leone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, July 4 (Xinhua) -- United Nations peacekeepers in Sierra
Leone said Tuesday that they have retaken the key town of Masiaka
which fell to the rebels on Monday night.
</P>
<P>
Officials said there had been heavy fighting between the rebels
and Indian and Jordanian units of the UN force, but gave no
details of casualties, reports reaching here from Freetown quoted
them as saying.
</P>
<P>
A UN spokeswoman said peacekeepers were now deployed in
strength in the town, which lies at a key crossroads, some 60
kilometers east of the capital, Freetown. 
</P>
</TEXT>
