<HEADLINE> Colombian Rebel ELN Destroys Two Energy Towers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BOGOTA, July 4 (Xinhua) -- Two electricity conducting towers
in rural zones of Colombia's northeastern Antioquia department
were destroyed Tuesday with explosives.
</P>
<P>
Authorities attributed the attacks to the rebel National
Liberation Army (ELN).
</P>
<P>
an official spokesperson said, as consequence of the attacks,
certain districts remained without electric fluid northeast of
Medellin, Antioquia's capital.
</P>
<P>
ELN, the second largest rebel group in Colombia, has destroyed
over 500 towers of electricity conduction, in protest against the
project to privatize energy generation and distribution firms.
</P>
</TEXT>
